            {
              "id": "CVE-2025-15281-glibc-langpack-en",
              "name": "RpmMatcherExactIndirectMatch",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "CVE-2025-15281 low vulnerability for glibc-langpack-en package"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "A flaw was found in glibc. When the wordexp function is called with the flags WRDE_REUSE and WRDE_APPEND, it may return uninitialized memory. If the caller inspects the we_wordv array or calls the wordfree function to free the allocated memory, the process will abort, resulting in a denial of service."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://github.com/anchore/grype",
              "help": {
                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2025-15281\nSeverity: low\nPackage: glibc-langpack-en\nVersion: 2.39-58.el10_1.7\nFix Version: \nType: rpm\nLocation: /usr/lib/sysimage/rpm/rpmdb.sqlite\nData Namespace: redhat:distro:redhat:10\nLink: [CVE-2025-15281](https://access.redhat.com/security/cve/CVE-2025-15281)",
